  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Field Hospital Support through German Red Cross</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Affected population(s)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The American Red Cross provided support to the German and Finnish Red Cross Societies for the operation of their field hospital located in Carrefour, just outside of Port au Prince. The field hospital opened immediately after the earthquake and continued to provide free medical services through the end of December 2010, treating over 70,000 patients. The hospital provided both fixed and mobile health services, as well as training for volunteers to provide psychosocial support and community health and hygiene promotion. In addition to supporting the operation of the hospital and the salaries of the staff, the American Red Cross is now providing support to rehabilitate a wall surrounding the soccer field that housed the hospital after the hospital shut down.</narrative>
  </description>
